TOTAL: 51 cards +3 Magi<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> 1st Magi- Hrada <br>
This guy can really slow down the opponent and give allow time to get a force prepared. The regional penality is cruel and annoying. I can not say for sure, but I believe that they can not play relics from any other region while their region is altered to shadow, I am a bit shady on that still. A great combo, but rare to get is 1st turn get out a creature with warriors boots, use shadow rain and hti their magi, could defeat them depending on which magi.<br>
<br>
2nd Magi- Chur<br>
Obviously opposing relics are dead now, if they have any out use vaporize, and her text wont let them get any more out without them being discarded immediatly. After that Chur is a great 6 energize magi, so send out creatures efficintly and wisely<br>
<br>
3rd Magi- Morag <br>
He has great energize. If it comes down to magi #3, then they will have relics stocked away in their because of Chur, so when they put a bunch out take advantge by letting out the shadow vinocs (ugger is a great combo with these guys), as well as taking control of the relics with Morag<br>
<br>
Some Other Card Choices-<br>
Chaos sphere- usually useful and useable for clean-up when morag is out<br>
Equilibriate- great against decks that add a lot of energy<br>
Agram&#39;s Armor- DEFENSE!!<br>
Stealth- awesome card to use against high energy creatures<br>
Szalalak- Yes he can be disarded with a simple dice roll, but if the roll is 1,2,5, or 6 then his purpose is well worth it<br>
<br>
Have fun Dueling<br>
